  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Exodus 29:35",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 29:35",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Seven days shalt thou consecrate them ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Though all the ceremonies were performed on the first day, yet they were not to look upon their consecration as completed till the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "seven days’ end, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which put a solemnity upon their admission, and a distance between this and their former state, and obliged them to enter upon their work with a pause, giving them time to consider the weight of it. This was to be observed in after ages: he that was to succeed Aaron in the high-priesthood, must put on the holy garments seven days together, in token of a deliberate advance into his office, and that one sabbath might pass over him in his consecration. Every day of the seven, in this first consecrations, a bullock was to be offered for a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sin-offering, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which was to intimate, 1st, That though atonement was made, yet they must still keep up a penitent sense of sin, and often repeat the confession of it. 2d, That those sacrifices which were thus offered day by day, could not make the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "comers thereunto perfect, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for then they would have ceased to be offered, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 10:1-2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". They must therefore expect the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "bringing in of a better hope. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Now this consecration of the priests was a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shadow of good things to come. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1st, Our Lord Jesus is the great High-Priest of our profession, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "called of God ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to be so ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "consecrated ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for evermore, anointed with the Spirit above his fellows, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "clothed ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "with the holy garments, even with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "glory ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "beauty, sanctified ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "by his own blood, not that of bullocks and rams. 2d, All believers are spiritual priests, to offer spiritual sacrifices, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Peter 2:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) washed in the blood of Christ, and so ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "made to our God priests, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 1:5-6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". They also are clothed with the beauty of holiness, and have received the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "anointing, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 2:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". 3d, It is likewise here intimated that gospel ministers are to be solemnly set apart to the work of the ministry with great deliberation and seriousness, both in the ordainers and in the ordained, as those that are employed in a great work, and intrusted with a great charge.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
