  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 35-37.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "The repetition of the ceremonial, and the consecration of the altar.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 35.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Seven days shalt thou consecrate them",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The repetition of the ceremony seven times on seven separate days seems to be intended. Thus was an ideal completeness given to it. Compare the seven days' compassing around of Jericho (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 6:3, 4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",), the seven washings in Jordan by Naaman (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 5:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), the seven ascents to the top of Carmel by the servant of Elijah (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 18:43, 44",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), etc. Exodus 29:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Consecration of Aaron and his Sons through the anointing of their persons and the offering of sacrifices, the directions for which form the subject of vv. 1-35. This can only be fully understood in connection with the sacrificial law contained in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 1-7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It will be more advisable therefore to defer the examination of this ceremony till we come to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the consecration itself is described. The same may also be said of the expiation and anointing of the altar, which are commanded in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 29:36",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 29:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and carried out in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 8:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]